data.text:
Steven Tyler’s daughter Liv Tyler hung with another famous rock kid, fashion designer Stella McCartney, at the launch for McCartney’s new store in New York City earlier this week. Last April, Pennsylvania publisher Rodale announced that it would be releasing a manners book by Liv Tyler (who’s apparently quite refined, despite her dad) and her Maine-based maternal grandmother, Dorothea Johnson, who founded the Protocol School of Washington. Rodale told us yesterday that the guide, which will be called “Modern Manners,’’ will be released later this year.
